{{Expand Japanese|難波小野王|date=January 2023}}
{{Infobox royalty |consort = yes |name = Princess Naniwa no Ono |succession = [[Empress of Japan|Empress consort of Japan]] |reign = 485-489 |spouse = [[Emperor Kenzō]] |issue = |royal house = [[Imperial House of Japan|Yamato]] |father = |mother = |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = 489 |death_place = |date of burial = |place of burial = |}}
'''Princess Naniwa no Ono''' (? – 489) was [[Empress of Japan]] as the consort of [[Emperor Kenzō]].<ref> Anston, W.G. (1896). Transactions and Proceedings of The Japan Society, London. Supplement I. Nihongi: Chronicles of Japan from the Earliest Times to A.D. 697. Vol. 1. London: Kegan Paul, Trench, Trüber, & Co.</ref>
Daughter of Prince Oka-no-Wakugo; great granddaughter of Emperor Yuryaku. Committed suicide due to fears over disrespecting Emperor Ninken when he was a Crown Prince.
==Notes== {{reflist}}
{{Consorts of Japan}}
{{DEFAULTSORT:Princess Naniwa no Ono}}
[[Category:Japanese empresses]] [[Category:Year of death missing]]
{{Japan-royal-stub}}

